OL,3,C'Wonderful' mum, 94, died after being
OL,4,Cstruck by seafront advertising board
OL,6,FMrs Carter was described by her family
OL,7,Fas having been "completely fit in both
OL,8,Fbody and mind" and determined to live
OL,9,Fto 100.
OL,11,FHer son, Michael Carter, told the
OL,12,Fcourt: "She was the most wonderful
OL,13,Fperson, full of life and energy, even
OL,14,Fat the age of 94."
OL,16,FHe added that Mrs Carter was an
OL,17,F"independent person", employing no
OL,18,Fcarers but just a gardener for her
OL,19,Fbungalow garden.
