OL,3,C'Wonderful' mum, 94, died after being
OL,4,Cstruck by seafront advertising board
OL,6,FHe told the court she was making the
OL,7,Fmost of lockdown having been lifted
OL,8,Fearlier that year, and had been
OL,9,Flooking forward to a coach trip she
OL,10,Fhad booked.
OL,12,FHe said: 'I just hope mum is in a
OL,13,Fbetter place now, smiling down on us.
OL,14,FAnd I hope lessons can be learnt from
OL,15,Fthe terrible events."
OL,17,FAll three of her children attended
OL,18,Fcourt, and Mr Carter read victim
OL,19,Fstatements from them all and from Mrs
OL,20,FCarter's son-in-law.
