OL,3,C'Wonderful' mum, 94, died after being
OL,4,Cstruck by seafront advertising board
OL,6,FSpeaking after the hearing, Mr Carter
OL,7,Fsaid: "As a family we just hope the
OL,8,FGrand Pier will learn from this tragic
OL,9,Fevent and ensure they but health and
OL,10,Fsafety measures in place for all
OL,11,Faspects of their operation of the
OL,12,FGrand Pier to ensure nothing like this
OL,13,Fever happens again.
OL,15,F"It is just a shame the owner of the
OL,16,FGrand Pier didn't have the common
OL,17,Fdecency to apologise personally after
OL,18,Fthe sentencing. Words cost nothing and
OL,19,Fit would have meant a lot to our
OL,20,Ffamily."
